<TITLE> City bus kills young boy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  A speeding bus killed an adolescent boy Wednesday morning at Bata signal point in the capital, police said. The victim was identified as Lavlu, son of Md. Delwar and inhabitant of 393, Ashraf Complex. Md. Hasan, an eyewitness told bdnews24.com the accident occurred at about 10:15 am he was travelling to Shahbagh as a passenger aboard a Shatabdi Poribahan bus. At the Bata signal crossing on Elephant Road he saw another Falguni Poribahan bus pushing pedestrian Lavlu violently aside as he was crossing the road. The bus driver and his helper fled leaving the bus. Kawsar, elder brother of the victim took him to Dhaka Medical College Hospital at 10:40 am where the duty doctor declared him dead. Abdul Mobin, sub-inspector, New Market police station told bdnews24.com the Falguni Poribahan bus bearing registration no. Dhaka Metro-Ga 11-3262 was seized and taken to the police station. bdnews2
